# Context Compaction Hook

## Activation

This rule applies when the user says any of:
- "summarize this chat"
- "compact the context"
- "compress this conversation"
- "create a new chat with context"
- "hand off to a new session"
- "save what we've done"

## Process

### 1. Summarize First
Run the `/summarize-chat` command to produce a structured summary of the conversation. This captures goals, decisions, file changes, and open items.

### 2. Compact Second
Run the `/compact-context` command to compress the summary + project state into a dense briefing document that can bootstrap a new chat.

### 3. Present to the User
After both are saved, tell the user:
- Where the summary was saved
- Where the compacted context was saved
- The exact prompt to paste into a new chat to continue seamlessly

## Proactive Trigger

If you notice the conversation has gone on for a very long time (many exchanges, multiple complex tasks completed), suggest compaction:

> "This session has covered a lot of ground. Want me to summarize and compact the context so you can continue in a fresh chat without losing anything?"
